article.headline: Chicago State 109, IND South Bend 73
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- David Holston scored 28 points while leading Chicago State to a 109-73 win over Indiana-South Bend on Tuesday night. Chicago State (7-14) shot 60.8 percent from the field, including 14-for-24 from 3-point range. Holston converted 8-of-12 3-pointers, and Royce Parran went 4-for-8 from behind the arc en route to 14 points for the game. Hubert Gentry scored 17 points and grabbed eight rebounds for Indiana-South Bend (7-12). Chicago State led 44-33 at halftime, then shot 74.3 percent over the final 20 minutes to pull away. Indiana-South Bend shot 41.2 percent from the field for the game, including 8-for-24 from 3-point range. Chicago State outscored Indiana-South Bend 23-4 on fast break points and outrebounded the Titans 44-33. John Cantrell added 26 points for the Cougars, and Kourtney Calvin chipped in 19 points and 12 rebounds.
